'Xfe' (X File Explorer) is a graphical file manager for the X Window System for
Unix and Unix-like systems, written by Roland Baudin. Its stated goals are
simplicity, lightness and ease of use. The xfe file manager uses the FOX toolkit
and is licensed under the terms of the GNU General Public License.
